:INFO
AzuraCast Technical Setup Guide
Step-by-step setup for self-hosting a community radio station on AzuraCast using a VPS. Assumes Ubuntu 22.04 and basic terminal comfort.

:TASK
[ ] Create a DigitalOcean or Vultr droplet with 1GB RAM minimum
[ ] Point your domain DNS A record to the droplet IP
[ ] SSH in and run the AzuraCast Docker install script
[ ] Complete the web-based setup wizard at port 80
[ ] Create a station and set the stream bitrate to 128kbps MP3
[ ] Add a DJ account for each show host with individual passwords
[ ] Upload AutoDJ playlist with at least 4 hours of music
[ ] Test the stream URL in VLC before announcing
[ ] Enable HTTPS via the built-in Let's Encrypt integration
[ ] Set up automated server backups via DigitalOcean snapshots

:NOTE
AzuraCast updates frequently. Run the built-in update command monthly from the admin panel. Keep your server's Docker version current to avoid compatibility issues.

:LINK
https://www.azuracast.com/docs
